WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'Linko' is a Workbench where you have to move a coloured
4-branch 'star' from the upper position to the exit, indicated by
a 'pressed-down' tile, located at the lowest part of a game board.

  As all tiles, except one, are occupied by the star or small
coloured squares, you can move only one small square or the star
at a time to the empty tile, just like in a sliding tile game...
so you may have to move a lot of small squares in order to
complete the game.

  To move an object (a star or a small coloured square) from one
tile to another, both tiles must be connected by a 'link', and of
course the other tile must be empty. A link can be switched so it
links to another tile, the 'starting' tile from where a link is
connected will always remain the same. By the way, even if some
tiles may be located next to each other diagonally, if they are
not connected by a link, no object (small square or star) can go
from one of those tiles to the other... besides, the game would be
too easy!

  The game includes many board patterns to complete, can you
complete each of them in the least amount of moves, without
losing patience, or getting a first class headache?

  Have fun!

